      "reviewer_notes": "Gate 4 (Exploitability) triggered DISPUTED_FP. Phase 03's code reading is factually correct: verify_data_column_sidecar (L532-561) validates array lengths only on the gossip path (L480), and RPC deserialization (codec.rs:696,717) plus database loads (hot_cold_store.rs:2529) bypass this validation. However, all data columns that reach KZG verification pass through validate_data_columns (kzg_utils.rs:49), which checks array length consistency at L84-86. Additionally, the KZG library itself has a dedicated defense-in-depth guard at kzg/lib.rs:250-258 with an explicit comment (L247-249) stating it exists 'to avoid any potential footguns'. This check returns InconsistentArrayLength error before any crypto operations, preventing the 'out-of-bounds panic or incorrect proof validation' that Phase 03 describes. Mitigated by KZG library's built-in array length validation. 01e reference: outputs/01e_PARTIAL_W2B3_1771748669.json, invariant: 'Column, kzg_commitments, and kzg_proofs arrays must all have equal length.' Severity remains HIGH as the property is spec-critical, but the specific attack path described is mitigated.",
